All the questions were leading. But the jurors were sharply critical of the interviewers' technique at the institute. Many of the interviews were conducted at an early stage of the sexual abuse investigation by MacFarlane, a social worker and director of the Child Sexual Abuse Center at Children's Institute International. What is in the interest of children is not always in the interest of the legal system, she said. A therapist defended her interviews of alleged victims in the McMartin Pre-School molestation trial, despite criticism by several jurors who said leading questions undermined the prosecution's case. 